<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2470] JMS clients stalled in case of many messages on a different queue - JDBC persistence</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2470</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With a large amount of messages in a Queue &amp;gt; 2M, the cleanup task takes a long time, maybe 20 minutes. Then it starts again immediately, which continually hogs the database as it locks out other users or other destinations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;direct JDBC persistence to external MySQL database, large amount of message on a queue. &lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12483077">AMQ-2470</key>
            <summary>JMS clients stalled in case of many messages on a different queue - JDBC persistence</summary>
